text: Duvan () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Duvansky Selsoviet, Duvansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 3,669 as of 2010. There are 44 streets. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Mesyagutovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Duvansky District Category:Ufa Governorate
title: Duvan
